   Up Arrow to Map   1. Abernathy Creek (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Abernathy Creek
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City: Longview


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            5 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - high water level would prevent using this ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From Longview, W on SR 4 10 mi; R on Abernathy Creek Rd; go 400 ft.;
        L on unmarked gravel Rd; go about .2 mi to access site.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle to moderate grade, and is located in a
        moderate to swift current. Some planks are broken planks and steel
        fasteners exposed. The ramp has become uneven due to erosion on the
        downstream side. No designated disabled parking. No overnight
        parking or camping at this site. There is no formal area designated
        for parking. Parking is available only along the road.


   Up Arrow to Map   2. Willow Grove Beach

        Waterbody: Columbia River
        Site Manager: Cowlitz County Parks & Rec
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Pumpout
     Trash Receptacles

                                Boat Launch Type:

                                  3 Loading Float
                                  4 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     75 Paved and Striped Spaces

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  25 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        In Longview, W on SR 4; L on SR 432 (Mt. Solo Rd); go .8 mi; R on
        Willow Grove Rd; go 4 mi; L at entrance to park.
        Site Description:

        The beach access has a gentle grade. The surface is sand which is
        loose and easy to get stuck in. Willow Grove Beach also has lawn
        areas, paved trails, picnic shelters, picnic tables, play equipment,
        flush restrooms, BBQ grills, drinking water, and beach access. An
        annual pass is available for $30 from the Cowlitz County Parks
        Department at (360) 577-3030. The website to view the boat launch
        facilities is http://www.co.cowlitz.wa.us.


