     20 Gravel Spaces
     10 Paved and Striped Spaces

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  75 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        On I-5, take Exit 30 (Kalama Exit); go to W side if I-5; R on Marine
        Drive; follow to end, 500 ft. past Port office.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a steep grade. The marina also offers boat
        moorage. Donations are requested for upkeep of the ramp. A park
        nearby offers a large lawn area, restrooms, and picnic tables.


   Up Arrow to Map   9. Modrow Bridge (WDFW) - Kalama River

        Waterbody: Kalama River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - high river levels may prevent the use of this ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From I-5, take Exit 32 (Kalama River Rd) E to Modrow Bridge Rd; R on
        Modrow Rd, cross Kalama River, immediate L to enter access site.
        Site Description:

        This boat ramp has gentle to moderate grade and is located on a
        section of river with a moderate current. Both sides of the ramp
        have moderate to severe undermining erosion. High water levels have
        washed away most of the gravel between the planks. The toe of the
        ramp appears to be undermined also. No designated disabled parking.
        No overnight parking or camping at this site.


   Up Arrow to Map   10. Mahaffey's Campground

        Waterbody: Kalama River
        Site Manager: Mahaffeys Campground
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            2 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Exit 32 (Kalama River Rd) on I-5, E on Kalama River Rd 2 mi.
        campground will be on R side of Rd.
        Site Description:

        This ramp has an abrupt drop off at the river bank. The gravel ramp
        material has been washed away by floods. The boat ramp is unsuitable
        for launching trailered boats, however hand launching is possible.
        The campground also has R.V. campsites with power and water hook-ups
        and a small picnic area. A natural gas pipeline crosses the Kalama
        River at this site.


   Up Arrow to Map   11. Upper Kalama (WDFW) - Kalama River

        Waterbody: Kalama River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Exit 32 (Kalama River Rd) on I-5, E on Kalama River Rd .5 mi
        past Lower Kalama Salmon Hatchery. Access site on R.
        Site Description:

        Silt and sand deposits from the river current have made the ramp
        unusable for trailered boats to launch. The ramp is located on the
        "outside" bend in the river, therefore, receives more current
        influences. No designated disabled parking. No overnight parking or
        camping at this site. Boaters utilizing this site have created an
        informal place to launch their boat next to the formal ramp.


   Up Arrow to Map   12. Pritchard's (WDFW) - Kalama River

        Waterbody: Kalama River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Asphalt Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            5 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From I-5 at Exit 32 (Kalama River Rd), E on Kalama River Rd 7 mi;
        site is just past Prichard's Western Anglers Store on R side of Rd.
        Site Description:

        This site is a hand launch site only. The site is a turnout of the
        Kalama River Road with a narrow asphalt ramp leading down to the
        river. Sand has accumulated at the ramp. The ramp is somewhat
        protected from the river current by a rock outcrop. A convenience
        store with bait, tackle, fishing licenses, food, and beverages is
        located across from the ramp.


   Up Arrow to Map   13. Dike Road - Woodland

        Waterbody: Columbia River
        Site Manager:
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            3 Natural Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     25 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            50 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Woodland; S on South Pekins Rd .5 mile; Turn R on Whalens Rd;
        go 1.5 mi; Turn L on Dike Rd; go approximately .5 mi; Turn R on a s;
        Rd; Several access spur Rds are to left.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp is the sand river bank. The sand is soft and loose.
        Traction may be difficult. The access has a moderate grade and is
        probably most suitable for hand launching and smaller watercraft. No
        designated disabled parking. Site is primitive with uneven and rough
        roads. Several piles of garbage have been dumped at this site. This
        site is used by ORV users also.


   Up Arrow to Map   14. Morgan Ramp - Lewis River

