        Site Manager:
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Asphalt Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     2 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            2 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From I-5 at Exit 16, W on NW 319th St, (becomes 41st Ave; n 324th
        St), approx 1 mi; At "Y", keep L on Allen Canyon Rd; keep to L on
        51st Ave, turn R on NW 304 St; go approx 1.75 mi to end of rd - boat
        ramp is on E side of RR trestle
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and is located on a section of
        the river with a slow current. The asphalt is breaking up at the end
        of the ramp resulting in a significant drop-off. Parking at this
        site is very limited.


   Up Arrow to Map   15. Horseshoe Lake Park (Cowlitz)

        Waterbody: Horseshoe Lake (Cowlitz Co.)
        Site Manager: Woodland City of
        Nearest City: Woodland


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                               Boat Launch Type:

                                 3 Asphalt Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     8 Paved and Striped Spaces

                               Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                 25 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        Going towards Woodland on I-5 take Exit 21 (Woodland Exit), go W on
        Goerig Rd .1 mi; S on Lake Shore Dr .2 mi; R just past Lakeside
        Motel; go .2 mi; L to park.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle grade and adequate traction. Asphalt is
        beginning to crack in places. Horseshoe Lake Park also has large
        lawn areas, a softball field, picnic tables, play equipment,
        drinking water, and picnic shelters. The park is closed from 10:00
        P.M. to 6:00 A.M.. No overnight camping. No personal watercraft
        allowed on Horseshoe Lake. Vehicle and trailer parking is designated
        along the street that borders the park.


   Up Arrow to Map   16. Lewis River Hatchery (WDFW)

        Waterbody: North Fork Lewis River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Woodland; E on SR 503; R (south) on Old Lewis River Rd; go .8
        mi to Lewis River Hatchery. Just past rearing pens, turn R; follow
        rough gravel Rd 400 to boat ramp.
        Site Description:

        At the time of the site visit, this ramp was covered by a massive
        amount of gravel and sand from the river, and appeared unusable. The
        concrete planks that are visible are broken and rebar is exposed.
        This ramp is below the Lewis River Hatchery pens.


   Up Arrow to Map   17. Merwin Ramp

        Waterbody: North Fork Lewis River
        Site Manager: PacifiCorp
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Natural Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - site is only open during daylight hours from Jan. 1 to Sept.
        30.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Woodland; E on SR 503 9 mi; R on Merwin Village Rd; go 1 mi; R
        on Merwin Hatchery Drive; go to end of Rd.
        Site Description:

        This is a primitive launching site that appears to be more suited
        for hand launching. The river access is rough because of the natural
        river rock surface. The ramp is protected from the river current by
        a rock jetty. The asphalt road at the boat ramp is crumbling. The
        parking for the boat ramp is about 700 feet from the ramp up a
        fairly steep hill. No designated parking. Nearby is the Merwin Dam
        Picnic Area which offers large lawn areas, picnic tables, and flush
        restrooms.


   Up Arrow to Map   18. Speelyai Bay Park

        Waterbody: Merwin Reservoir
        Site Manager: PacifiCorp
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Water Available

                                Boat Launch Type:

                                  2 Concrete Ramp
                                  2 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     20 Paved and Striped Spaces

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  30 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the park is closed during the winter.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the ramp is out of the water during times the reservoir is
        lowered.

        Driving Directions:

        From Woodland; E on SR 503 21 mi; R at Speelyai Bay Recreation Area
        sign; go .5 mi; at hairpin turn, turn R to Speelyai Bay Park.
        Site Description:

        The ramp is in good condition. It appears that a new mid section to
        the ramp was added recently. The boat ramp is out of the water
        during periods when the reservoir is lowered. Speelyai Bay Park also
        has a lawn area, picnic tables, picnic shelter, swimming beach, and
        fishing dock. No overnight parking or camping is allowed at this
        park.


   Up Arrow to Map   19. Cresap Bay Recreation Area

        Waterbody: Merwin Reservoir
        Site Manager: PacifiCorp
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Shower
     Water Available

                                Boat Launch Type:

                                  3 Concrete Ramp
                                  2 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     20 Paved and Striped Spaces

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  30 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - park is closed during the winter months.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Woodland; E on SR 503 23 mi; At SR503/Spur SR 503 junction,
        turn R (south); follow SR 503 another 3 mi; R on unmarked paved Rd
        to enter park; follow 1 mi down hill.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp is constructed with A 60 degree V-groove surface which
        provides excellent traction; Cresap Bay Park is a newly constructed
        facility that has a campground, large lawn areas, swim beach, picnic
        tables, boat moorage, play equipment, a group camping area, several
        restrooms, R.V. dump station, firewood access, public phone, R.V.
        campsites furnished with picnic tables and fire rings, and a nature
        trail. No overnight camping is allowed in the day-use area.


   Up Arrow to Map   20. Saddle Dam Recreation Area

        Waterbody: Yale Reservoir
        Site Manager: PacifiCorp
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                               Boat Launch Type:

                                 1 Loading Float
                                 2 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     20 Gravel Spaces
     2 Paved and Striped Spaces

                               Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                 20 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the park is closed during the winter.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the ramp is out of the water when the reservoir level is
        lowered.

        Driving Directions:

        From Woodland; E on SR 503 23 mi; S SR503 3 mi. L (east) on Frasier
        Rd; go 1.5 mi to park entrance.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a few broken planks and exposed rebar. The ramp is
        also fortified by a concrete bulkhead. The boat ramp is out of the
        water when the reservoir level is lowered. Saddle Dam Park also has
        R.V. campsites with picnic tables and fire rings, a day-use area
        with picnic tables and fire rings, a flush restroom, R.V. dump
        station, and drinking water. No overnight parking in the day-use
        area.


   Up Arrow to Map   21. Yale Park Recreation Area

        Waterbody: Yale Reservoir
        Site Manager: PacifiCorp
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            4 Concrete Ramp
                            2 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     20 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            40 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the boat ramp is out of the water during periods when the
        reservoir level is lowered.

        Driving Directions:

        From Woodland; E on SR 503 28 mi; R at entrance sign to Yale Park.
        boat ramp is 300 ft. directly S of park entrance.
        Site Description:

        The ramp is in excellent condition, and is composed of 60 degree
        V-groove which provides excellent traction. Rip-rap surrounds the
        ramp to prevent erosion. Rocks and debris do accumulate at the lower
        end of the ramp. The ramp is out of the water during the winter when
        the reservoir level is dropped preventing larger boats from
        launching, but smaller vessels can still hand launch and load. Yale
        Park also offers a picnic shelter, picnic tables, flush restrooms,
        swimming access, and lawn areas. An R.V. dump station is located
        across the road (SR 503) from the park entrance. The restrooms are
        locked during the winter. No overnight parking or camping is allowed
        in Yale Park.


   Up Arrow to Map   22. Cougar Camp and Park

        Waterbody: Yale Reservoir
        Site Manager: PacifiCorp
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Loading Float
                            3 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     25 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            50 Gravel Spaces
                            2 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the park and campground are closed during the winter months.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the boat ramp is out of the water when the reservoir level is
        dropped.

        Driving Directions:

        From Woodland; E on SR 503 31 mi; R just after crossing Panamaker
        Creek to enter campground, n 500 ft. to boat ramp.
        Site Description:

        The concrete planks are in good condition. The sides of the ramp are
        fortified with a concrete bulkhead. Panamaker Creek does deposit
        debris at the ramp. Cougar Park is across the creek from the boat
        launch. The park has a large lawn area, flush restrooms, picnic
        tables, play equipment, and a fishing dock. A bridge crossing the
        creek connects the park to the campground area. Cougar Campground
        has R.V. campsites with picnic tables, fire rings, and water access.
        Boat moorage is discouraged at the loading float area. No overnight
        parking in the day-use area.


   Up Arrow to Map   23. Beaver Bay Recreation Area

        Waterbody: Yale Reservoir
        Site Manager: PacifiCorp
        Nearest City: Cougar


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            40 Gravel Spaces
                            2 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the park is closed during the winter months.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the ramp is out of the water when the reservoir level is
        dropped.

        Driving Directions:

        From Woodland; E on SR 503 33 mi; R (south) on Sherman Rd; go .25 mi
        to entrance of park.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp is protected by bank cuts and reinforced by concrete
        planks placed on the banks. the boat ramp collects gravel and
        debris. Beaver Bay Recreation Area also consists of campsites with
        fire rings and picnic tables, R.V. dump station, public phone, flush
        restrooms, a picnic shelters, lawn area, and swim beach. No
        overnight parking in the day-use area.


