                                 25 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From I-5 at Exit 49, E on SR 504, 8 mi; R (south) on Kerr Rd; follow
        to end; R at end of county Rd to enter WDFW access area.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has broken concrete planks and is eroded on both
        sides. Steel fasteners are exposed. No overnight parking or camping
        is allowed. The paved trail to the loading float has eroded away at
        a section near the float. The loading float is slightly listing to
        the right. WDFW plans to pave the parking lot area, add a second
        vault toilet, install 5 picnic tables, and install 2 oil/water
        separators at this site.


   Up Arrow to Map   27. Silver Lake Motel & Resort - Cowlitz Co.

        Waterbody: Silver Lake (Cowlitz Co.)
        Site Manager: Silver Lake Motel and Resort
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                               Boat Launch Type:

                                 1 Concrete Ramp
                                 1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     8 Paved and Striped Spaces

                               Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                 None

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From I-5 take Exit 49, E on SR 504 6 mi; R to resort.
        Site Description:

        Silver Lake Motel and Resort also has boat moorage, boat rentals,
        convenience store, rental cabins, picnic area, fish cleaning
        station, play equipment, R.V. campsites with hookups, and public
        phone. No designated disabled parking. A fee is charged to use the
        ramp ($4.00/non-resort campers, $2.00/resort campers). Boat trailers
        must be parked separate from vehicles.


   Up Arrow to Map   28. Camp Kalama R.V. Park and Campground

        Waterbody: Kalama River
        Site Manager: Camp Kalama RV Park
        Nearest City: Kalama


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            15 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river level may be too high or too low to use the boat
        ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From I-5 at Exit 32, E .1 mi; R on Meeker Dr; go .2 mi; L to Camp
        Kalama R.V. Park; Campground.
        Site Description:

        Please note that the map shows the incorrect location for this ramp
        - it is on the Kalama River, not the Toutle River as shown. The boat
        ramp has a moderate to steep grade and is located on a section of
        river with a slow current. The boat ramp is protected, somewhat, by
        bankcuts and offers adequate traction. Camp Kalama R.V. Park and
        Campground also offers R.V. campsites with hookups, play equipment,
        a shuttle service to upriver sites, fish cleaning stations, game
        room, flush restrooms with showers, and public phones. A fee is
        charged for the use of the ramp ($2.00/in, $2.00/out). No designated
        disabled parking.


   Up Arrow to Map   29. Hog Island

        Waterbody: Cowlitz River
        Site Manager: Cowlitz County Parks & Rec
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     15 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            25 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        Just W of Castle Rock at SR 411 & Hwy # 10 intersection, N on W Side
        Hwy 5.7 mi; access site is on E side of Rd.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate current at the toe of the boat ramp.
        The ramp is somewhat protected from the river current by the bank
        cuts. The ramp receives silt deposited when the river is at a high
        level. There are 2 ramp areas at this site. The first is to the
        north of the parking area and the 2nd is east of the parking area
        and across a wooden bridge. No overnight parking or camping at this
        site. No designated disabled parking.


   Up Arrow to Map   30. Olequa (WDFW) - Cowlitz River

        Waterbody: Cowlitz River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Natural Ramp
                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            30 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From I-5 at Exit 52, take Barnes Drive NW 3.5 mi; N on Imboden Rd .2
        mi; W on Miekler Rd .25 mi to end of Rd at access site.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and is located in a moderate
        current. The concrete planks are in good condition, but the gravel
        between the planks is beginning to wash away. A natural ramp is
        south of the concrete plank ramp. No overnight parking or camping at
        this site. No designated disabled parking.



